# Benchmark dataset is the user's REAL personal memories — NEVER commit.
# Privacy hard-rule (research task brief): corpus/queries/qrels stay LOCAL.
# NOTE: both the trailing-slash (real dir) and bare-name (SYMLINK into the
# preserved artifacts at ~/.claude/claude-memory/benchmark-artifacts) forms are
# listed — git treats a symlink as a file, so `data/` alone would NOT ignore a
# `data` symlink and the real corpus could leak. Keep both forms.
data/
data
# Post-cleanup store snapshots (scripts/snapshot_corpus.py) are ALSO the user's
# real memories — same hard-rule, both forms kept for symlink safety.
snapshots/
snapshots
.venv/
cache/
cache
*.npy
*.faiss
*.db
# Cached LLM-extracted triples (derived from real memories) — gitignored.
triples_*.jsonl

# The eval-set GENERATOR embeds real memory-derived query text + author notes
# (paraphrases of real memories, real ids/notes). Treat it as a data artifact:
# LOCAL-ONLY, never commit. Regenerates data/ from corpus.jsonl. The HARNESS
# itself (harness/*.py, the other scripts) contains NO real content and is safe.
scripts/build_eval_set.py

# Python noise
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.pytest_cache/
*.egg-info/
.ipynb_checkpoints/

# Results from runs may quote real content — keep local by default.
results/
*.results.json
